blockStates.name: Projectile Motion
blockStates.userText:
This page shows the visual code 
for projectile motion. The x and y
coordinates as a function of time
are determined by the following
equations:

x = vcos(θ)t
y = vsin(θ)t - gt²/2

where v is the initial speed, θ is 
the initial angle, and g is the 
gravitational acceleration.

The time it takes the object to hit 
the ground is:

T = 2vsin(θ)/g
